dary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Echyngham was born about 1337, in Sussex, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir James Echyngham and Joan Dakeney. He married Joan Atte Gate about 1367. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 20 March 1413, in his hometown, at the age of 77."},"et":{"about 1337–20 March 1413":"umbes 1337–20. märts 1413","1334–1388":"1334–1388","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1336–Male":"1336–Surnud","1337–1413":"1337–1413","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1374–1464":"1374–1464","1272–1350":"1272–1350","–1350":"–1350","20 March 1413":"20. märts 1413","ABT 1367":"umbes 1367","1374":"1374","1350":"1350","1272":"1272","22 August 1350":"22. august 1350","1337":"1337","1413":"1413","1336":"1336","1335":"1335","1334":"1334","1388":"1388","1464":"1464","about 1337":"umbes 1337","about 1374":"umbes 1374","Echingham, Sussex, England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, , England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"fi":{"about 1337–20 March 1413":"noin 1337–20. maaliskuuta 1413","1334–1388":"1334–1388","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1336–Male":"1336–Kuollut","1337–1413":"1337–1413","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1374–1464":"1374–1464","1272–1350":"1272–1350","–1350":"–1350","20 March 1413":"20. maaliskuuta 1413","ABT 1367":"noin 1367","1374":"1374","1350":"1350","1272":"1272","22 August 1350":"22. elokuuta 1350","1337":"1337","1413":"1413","1336":"1336","1335":"1335","1334":"1334","1388":"1388","1464":"1464","about 1337":"noin 1337","about 1374":"noin 1374","Echingham, Sussex, England":"Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sussex, , England":"